Introduction

FIESTAR is an independent South Korean girl group formed in 2012 by LOEN Entertainment and signed under FAVE Entertainment.

They originally debuted with six members on August 31, 2012 with the single album "Vista".

They disbanded on May 15, 2018 after four of the members' contracts ended on April 30 and decided not to renew.

On May 22, 2024, Cao Lu shared that she had bought partial copyrights of their previous singles with an intent to re-record them in Chinese. They announced their reunion with a comeback on August 30, 2024. On August 27, 2024, news outlet Sports Chosun reported that FIESTAR will be making their comeback on August 31,2024 to celebrate their twelve years anniversary with a remake of their 2015 song "You're Pitiful". Member Cao Lu was reported to have invested in this project. On August 31, 2024 they released the digital single "You're Pitiful - 2024 Ver.".
